<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1348,1798]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Regarding 
<taxonomicName authority="Mannerheim, 1829" authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1829" box="[323,700,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onthophagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirculus">
<emphasis box="[323,458,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. hirculus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mannerheim C. G." box="[470,700,1348,1374]" journalOrPublisher="Nouveaux memoires de la Societe imperiale des naturalistes de Moscou" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="29 - 80" part="7" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103533page/61/mode/1up" refId="ref9281" refString="Mannerheim C. G. 1829. Description de quarante nouvelles especes de scarabeides du Bresil avec figures. Nouveaux memoires de la Societe imperiale des naturalistes de Moscou 7 (1): 29 - 80. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 103533  page / 61 / mode / 1 up [accessed 28 Mar. 2018]." title="Description de quarante nouvelles especes de scarabeides du Bresil avec figures" type="journal article" year="1829">Mannerheim, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, we found one female specimen at MZH whose original labels (
<figureCitation box="[273,360,1383,1409]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[200,1395,925,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1398,914,1886]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. A–B. Dorsal habitus of the lectotype and paralectotype of Onthophagus hircus Billberg, 1815. C. Dorsal habitus of the lectotype of O. hirculus Mannerheim, 1829. D–E. Labels of the types of O. hircus Billberg, 1815. F. Labels of the type of O. hirculus Mannerheim, 1829." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1251600/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
) led us to consider this singleton as a syntype of this species name. Indeed, the “Ménétr” label refers undoubtedly to the French ornithologist and entomologist Edouard Ménétriés. From December 1823 to January 1824, Ménétriés was recruited by Baron G.H. von de Langsdorff to collect specimens around Tijuco (Minas Gerais) and particularly across the Serra da Lapa (
<bibRefCitation author="Mannerheim C. G." box="[1172,1394,1489,1515]" journalOrPublisher="Nouveaux memoires de la Societe imperiale des naturalistes de Moscou" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="29 - 80" part="7" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103533page/61/mode/1up" refId="ref9281" refString="Mannerheim C. G. 1829. Description de quarante nouvelles especes de scarabeides du Bresil avec figures. Nouveaux memoires de la Societe imperiale des naturalistes de Moscou 7 (1): 29 - 80. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 103533  page / 61 / mode / 1 up [accessed 28 Mar. 2018]." title="Description de quarante nouvelles especes de scarabeides du Bresil avec figures" type="journal article" year="1829">Mannerheim 1829</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero N." box="[297,480,1524,1551]" journalOrPublisher="Vol. I. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1750 - 1905" publicationUrl="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.101715" refId="ref9826" refString="Papavero N. 1971. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology, with Special Reference to Collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. I. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 101715" title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology, with Special Reference to Collectors" type="book chapter" year="1971">Papavero 1971</bibRefCitation>
). Although Mannerheim in the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1829" box="[1149,1284,1524,1551]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onthophagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirculus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1284,1524,1551]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. hirculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not mention whether the specimens of the type series were collected by Ménétriés, he says the specimens were collected in Tijuco, which surely refers to the Arraial do Tejuco, the former name of the current municipality of Diamantina, Minas Gerais. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero N." box="[883,1084,1630,1657]" journalOrPublisher="Vol. I. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1750 - 1905" publicationUrl="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.101715" refId="ref9826" refString="Papavero N. 1971. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology, with Special Reference to Collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. I. Museu de Zoologia, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Brazil. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 101715" title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology, with Special Reference to Collectors" type="book chapter" year="1971">Papavero (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, the material collected by Ménétriés, de Langsdorff and Moritz Rugenda (the artist of the expedition) was partly sent to the Museum of Berlin, while 6 boxes of natural history specimens were sent to the Academy of Science of Saint Petersburg. The specimens belonging to the type series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1829" box="[938,1068,1736,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onthophagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirculus">
<emphasis box="[938,1068,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. hirculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were then incorporated into Mannerheim’s personal collection, which is today deposited at MZH (
<bibRefCitation author="Horn W. &amp; Kahle I. &amp; Friese G. &amp; Gaedike R." box="[1010,1208,1771,1797]" journalOrPublisher="Akademie der Landwirtschaftswissenschaften der DDR, Berlin" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref8959" refString="Horn W., Kahle I., Friese G. &amp; Gaedike R. 1990. Collectiones entomologicae. Ein Kompendium uber den Verbleib entomologischer Sammlungen der Welt bis 1960. Teil I: A bis K; Teil II: L bis Z. Akademie der Landwirtschaftswissenschaften der DDR, Berlin." title="Collectiones entomologicae. Ein Kompendium uber den Verbleib entomologischer Sammlungen der Welt bis 1960. Teil I: A bis K; Teil II: L bis Z" type="book" year="1990">
Horn 
<emphasis box="[1079,1138,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1398,1833,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
While the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1829" box="[481,612,1833,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onthophagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirculus">
<emphasis box="[481,612,1833,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. hirculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on at least one male and one female, we have so far not been able to find any male specimen attributable to the type series.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1930,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Thus, to preserve the nomenclatural stability for these species names, we designate as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1815" box="[189,298,1965,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onthophagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hircus">
<emphasis box="[189,298,1965,1992]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. hircus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the male belonging to the syntypic series, while the female is labelled as paralectotype. The only known surviving type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mannerheim" authorityYear="1829" box="[662,792,2001,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onthophagus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirculus">
<emphasis box="[662,792,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">O. hirculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here designated as lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
